#: ../../docs/classes/class_rigidbody.rst:166
msgid "enum **Mode**:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_rigidbody.rst:168
msgid ""
"**MODE_RIGID** = **0** --- Rigid body mode. This is the \"natural\" state"
" of a rigid body. It is affected by forces, and can move, rotate, and be "
"affected by user code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_rigidbody.rst:170
msgid ""
"**MODE_STATIC** = **1** --- Static mode. The body behaves like a "
":ref:`StaticBody <class_StaticBody>`, and can only move by user code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_rigidbody.rst:172
msgid ""
"**MODE_CHARACTER** = **2** --- Character body mode. This behaves like a "
"rigid body, but can not rotate."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_rigidbody.rst:174
msgid ""
"**MODE_KINEMATIC** = **3** --- Kinematic body mode. The body behaves like"
" a :ref:`KinematicBody <class_KinematicBody>`, and can only move by user "
"code."
msgstr ""

