msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_rigidbody.rst:362
msgid "set_use_continuous_collision_detection(value)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_rigidbody.rst:364
msgid "is_using_continuous_collision_detection()"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_rigidbody.rst:367
msgid "If ``true``, continuous collision detection is used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_rigidbody.rst:369
msgid ""
"Continuous collision detection tries to predict where a moving body will "
"collide, instead of moving it and correcting its movement if it collided."
" Continuous collision detection is more precise, and misses fewer impacts"
" by small, fast-moving objects. Not using continuous collision detection "
"is faster to compute, but can miss small, fast-moving objects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_rigidbody.rst:375
msgid ":ref:`bool <class_bool>` **custom_integrator**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_rigidbody.rst:380
msgid "set_use_custom_integrator(value)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_rigidbody.rst:382
msgid "is_using_custom_integrator()"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_rigidbody.rst:385
msgid ""
"If ``true``, internal force integration will be disabled (like gravity or"
" air friction) for this body. Other than collision response, the body "
"will only move as determined by the :ref:`_integrate_forces "
"<class_RigidBody_method__integrate_forces>` function, if defined."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_rigidbody.rst:391
msgid ":ref:`float <class_float>` **gravity_scale**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_rigidbody.rst:396
msgid "set_gravity_scale(value)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_rigidbody.rst:398
msgid "get_gravity_scale()"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_rigidbody.rst:401
msgid ""
"This is multiplied by the global 3D gravity setting found in **Project > "
"Project Settings > Physics > 3d** to produce RigidBody's gravity. For "
"example, a value of 1 will be normal gravity, 2 will apply double "
"gravity, and 0.5 will apply half gravity to this object."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_rigidbody.rst:407
msgid ":ref:`float <class_float>` **linear_damp**"
msgstr ""

